
   COMPUNET UPDATE, March 27th 1990  

Since we gave you the sorry news of
Fastrak's back down from their agreement
we have spent most of the time speaking
to other networks. These have included
Mercury and a brand new company named
National Networks. As you may have read,
Fastrak have agreed to help Compunet
to set up on any network we choose.

Meanwhile, at the new office in Camden,
Telecom have informed us that new direct
access lines will be installed on April
26th. Last time (when they gave us a
date for installing the voice lines)
they actually did the work around 2
weeks earlier than promised. So, with a
bit of luck from BT, we could have
direct access to the main system in
around 14 days.
